Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
resetModifiedBudget(25.10)                          resetModifiedBudget(25.10)

Name
       resetModifiedBudget  -  Resets  the  budget that was modified using the
       modifyBudget command

Syntax
       resetModifiedBudget

       {-ptn <partitionName> | -inst <instanceName>}

       -pin <pinName>

       [-setup | -hold]

       [-view <viewName>]

       [-help]

       Resets the budget that was modified using the modifyBudget command. re-
       setModifiedBudget allows you to revert to the original generated budget
       if the modified budget is not yielding the correct timing for a  block,
       or rectify an incorrectly modified budget.

Parameters
       -pin<pinName>
              Specifies the name of the pin for which manual budgets are to be
              reset. You can use * to specify all pins.

       -hold  Specifies to reset the hold information.

       -inst<instanceName>
              Specifies the name of the hierarchical instance for which manual
              budgets are to be reset.

       -help  Outputs the command usage.

       -ptn<partitionName>
              Specifies the name of the partition for which manual budgets are
              to be reset.

       -setup Specifies to reset the setup information.

       -view <viewName>
              Resets the budget for the specified view.

Example
              * The  following command resets the modified budget data for the
                instance inst1:

                resetModifiedBudget -inst inst1

Related Information
       The "Modifying Budgets" section in the Timing Budgeting chapter of  the
       User Guide document.

